The secondary aim of this study was to evaluate the relationship between changes in impedance and standard outcome measures used to characterize impairment in the clinic. ΔStiffness scores were calculated for each participant and linearly regressed on each clinical measure (6MWT, 10MWT, LEFM, MAS). For each limb, stiffness as a function of percent stance phase was determined using an interpolation. A ΔStiffness score was then defined as the average absolute difference in stiffness between the paretic and non-paretic limbs across the stance phase. The same protocol was used to define ΔDamping scores.5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
